entry.name: rbmnodomain
entry.text: RBM: Cannot extract domain from request
entry.description: The user for the request is not associated with a domain. This is an internal error.
entry.suggestion: Contact IBM Support.

entry.name: rbmaufailed
entry.text: RBM: Authentication failed - Access Denied
entry.description: User authentication failed because the user does not exist or the password did not match. If a remote authentication service is configured, you might also not be able to connect to it. This message could indicate a break-in attempt.
entry.suggestion: Verify the correct spelling of the user and password. Check if CAPS-Lock was mistakenly enabled. When using a remote authentication service, check if the service is up and that the user exists. You can enable RBM debugging from the Troubleshooting screen.

entry.name: rbmnocred
entry.text: RBM: No user access policy - Access Denied
entry.description: RBM could not map the user to a valid access policy. This failure usually indicates a configuration error in the map credentials phase of RBM. The user was authenticated but failed to match to any access policy.
entry.suggestion: Verify the configuration in the map credentials phase of RBM. Verify that the mapping from the user name to the access profile exists. You can enable RBM debugging from the Troubleshooting screen.

entry.name: rbminvfileop
entry.text: RBM: Attempted invalid file operation - Access denied.
entry.description: A file operation is violating static directory access permission, which could be attempting to write to a read-only directory or reading from a write-only directory. This violation could indicate a break-in attempt.

entry.name: rbmpolicydef1
entry.text: RBM: Policies contradict, use default - Access allowed.
entry.description: The user credentials have conflicting access policies of equal weight. In this case, RBM bases its decision on the default policy, which is 'allow all'.
entry.suggestion: Review the access policy of the user. RBM uses the longest best match algorithm to assign weights to individual policy statements.

entry.name: rbmpolicydef2
entry.text: RBM: Policies contradict, use default - Access denied.
entry.description: The user credentials have conflicting access policies of equal weight. In this case, RBM bases its decision on the default policy, which is 'deny all' unless overwritten by the user.
entry.suggestion: Review the access policy of the user. RBM uses the longest best match algorithm to assign weights to individual policy statements.

entry.name: rbmnoxmlfile
entry.text: RBM: Missing or corrupt RBM information file.
entry.description: The map credentials phase of RBM is configured to use an XML file. This file either does not exist or cannot be parsed.
entry.suggestion: Review the RBM map credentials phase. Verify that the RBM information file exists and is valid XML.

entry.name: rbmbadxmlfile
entry.text: RBM: Unsupported version of the RBM information file.
entry.description: The map credentials phase of RBM is configured to use an XML file. The firmware does not support the format version of this file.
entry.suggestion: Change the format version to a supported value in the XML file.

entry.name: xmlmgmtinvservice
entry.text: Invalid service URI for the XML management interface.
entry.description: The service URI for the XML management interface is invalid. The request was not processed.
entry.suggestion: Verify the service URI.

entry.name: xmlmgmtnoservice
entry.text: Requested XML management interface service is disabled.
entry.description: The requested XML management interface service is disabled. The request was not processed.
entry.suggestion: Verify the configuration of the XML management interface. You can enable and disable individual services.

entry.name: rbminvcred
entry.text: Missing or incomplete user credentials.
entry.description: The user credentials to access the XML management interface are missing or incomplete. Accessing the XML management interface requires valid credentials. Valid credentials are usually user name and password through HTTP basic authentication.
entry.suggestion: Verify the RBM configuration to determine the type of user credentials. Verify your request to ensure that it contains the required credentials.

entry.name: rbmazfailed
entry.text: RBM: Authorization failed - Access denied.
entry.description: The user failed to authorize. The user attempted an action that is not permitted under the defined access policy.
entry.suggestion: If this failure is not intentional, add permission for this action to this user in the RBM access policy.

entry.name: profilerbmerror
entry.text: Profile Conformance: Authorization failed - Access denied.
entry.description: The user failed to authorize. The user attempted to run the profile checker, and the access policy does not permit this action. Running a profile checker requires read permission to the configurations being profiled.
entry.suggestion: If this failure is not intentional, add permission for this action to this user in the RBM access policy.

entry.name: profilecfgerror
entry.text: Profile Conformance: Requested configuration does not exist.
entry.description: A profile conformance request was made for a configuration that does not exist. There was no matching configuration for the request.
entry.suggestion: Check that the name of the configuration was correctly entered in the request.

entry.name: profilecheckererror
entry.text: Profile Conformance: Requested checker could not be run.
entry.description: A profile conformance request failed, because the requested profile checker could not be run.
entry.suggestion: Verify that the checker XSLT compiles and that the requested checker is in the store:///profiles/ directory.

entry.name: wspdomainerror
entry.text: Policy Mapping: Invalid domain in mapping request.
entry.description: A policy mapping request failed, because the domain in the mapping request is invalid.
entry.suggestion: Verify the domain in the policy mapping request.

entry.name: wspnserror
entry.text: Policy Mapping: No matching namespace mapping found.
entry.description: A policy mapping request failed, because no matching namespace mapping stylesheet was found.
entry.suggestion: Verify the namespace of your policy domain. Verify that a mapping stylesheet for the namespace of your policy domain is in the store:///policies/mappings/ (default mapping stylesheets), the store:///policies/custom/ (global custom mapping stylesheets), or the policy: (domain local mapping stylesheets) directory.

entry.name: wspinterror
entry.text: Policy Mapping: Internal Error.
entry.description: A policy mapping request failed because of an internal error.
entry.suggestion: Contact IBM Support.

entry.name: wspactionerror
entry.text: Policy Mapping: Generated configuration contains an action without an @assertionNo attribute.
entry.description: The policy mapping failed due to invalid configuration. The generated configuration contains an action without an @assertionNo attribute. The @assertionNo attribute is required to allow the sequencing of the generated actions in the processing rule.
entry.suggestion: Verify your mapping stylesheet, and ensure that each generated action contains an @assertionNo attribute. If you do not have a custom mapping stylesheet, contact IBM Support.

entry.name: secpolclientcertnoresp
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Ignoring RequireClientCertificate assertion in a response action.
entry.description: A policy subject contains a RequireClientCertificate WS-Security Policy assertion in a calculated effective policy alternative. The policy for the policy subject applies to the response-side message flow. The TLS client certificate policy assertion will be enforced for request messages but ignored for the corresponding response messages.

entry.name: secpolbasicauthnoresp
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Ignoring HttpBasicAuthentication assertion in a response action.
entry.description: A policy subject contains a HttpBasicAuthentication WS-Security Policy assertion in a calculated effective policy alternative. The policy for the policy subject applies to the response-side message flow. The HTTP basic authentication policy assertion will be enforced for request messages but ignored for the corresponding response messages.

entry.name: rbmrestrictedadmin
entry.text: RBM: Log in of 'admin' restricted - Access denied.
entry.description: The login attempt by the 'admin' account was denied. The RBM configuration allows the restriction of the 'admin' account to log in through only the serial connection.
entry.suggestion: Contact the system administrator of your DataPower Gateway to obtain a valid user account or to remove the access restrictions for the 'admin' account.

entry.name: rbmrestrictedfallback
entry.text: RBM: Restricted login mode - Access denied.
entry.description: The login attempt of the user in fallback mode was denied. The RBM configuration allows a subset of local users to log in when in fallback mode.
entry.suggestion: Contact the system administrator of your DataPower Gateway to add the user to the list of allowed fallback users.

entry.name: rbminternalerror
entry.text: RBM: Resource access denied.
entry.description: The access of the user to a resource was denied.
entry.suggestion: Check the RBM access profile of the user that denies or allows access to the requested resource.

entry.name: secpolfilternosign
entry.text: Ignoring signing-related assertion in filter mode
entry.description: A signing-related assertion was found in a response-side alternative in filter mode, which indicates that the message should be signed. In filter policy mode, the input message cannot be altered. The assertion will be ignored.
entry.suggestion: If the message should be signed, change the policy mode from filter to enforce. Alternatively, remove the signing-related assertion from the effective WS-Policy for this policy subject.

entry.name: secpolfilternoencrypt
entry.text: Ignoring encryption-related assertion in filter mode
entry.description: An encryption-related assertion was found in a response-side alternative in filter mode, which indicates that the message should be encrypted. In filter mode, the input message cannot be altered. The assertion will be ignored.
entry.suggestion: If the message should be encrypted, change the policy mode from filter to enforce. Alternatively, remove the encryption-related assertion from the effective WS-Policy for this policy subject.

entry.name: secpolnotoken
entry.text: No child token assertion found for binding
entry.description: Cannot find the required child token assertion for the AsymmetricBinding or SymmetricBinding assertion. One of the following child token assertions is required: ProtectionToken, EncryptionToken, InitiatorToken, or InitiatorEncryptionToken.
entry.suggestion: Add the appropriate child token assertion to the AsymmetricBinding or SymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: secpoltransbindingnotendpoint
entry.text: Found transport assertion attached to non-endpoint policy subject.
entry.description: Found a TransportBinding or TransportToken assertion attached to a non-endpoint policy subject. A transport assertion can be attached to only an endpoint subject.
entry.suggestion: Attach the transport assertion to an endpoint policy subject.

entry.name: rbmnouser
entry.text: RBM: Cannot extract user from request.
entry.description: The request is not associated with a user. This is an internal error.
entry.suggestion: Contact IBM Support.

entry.name: secpolsymbindingwrongsubject
entry.text: Found SymmetricBinding attached to improper policy subject.
entry.description: A SymmetricBinding assertion is attached to an improper policy subject. SymmetricBinding assertions should be applied to endpoint policy subjects and can be applied to operation policy subjects. Attaching the assertion to a different policy subject is not recommended.
entry.suggestion: Associate the SymmetricBinding assertion to an endpoint or operation policy subject.

entry.name: secpolasymbindingwrongsubject
entry.text: Found AsymmetricBinding attached to improper policy subject.
entry.description: An AsymmetricBinding assertion is attached to an improper policy subject. AsymmetricBinding assertions should be applied to endpoint policy subjects and can be applied to operation policy subjects. Attaching the assertion to a different policy subject is not recommended.
entry.suggestion: Associate the AsymmetricBinding assertion to an endpoint or operation policy subject.

entry.name: secpolsymbindnotoken
entry.text: Found SymmetricBinding without child protection assertion.
entry.description: Did not find a child protection assertion for the SymmetricBinding assertion. SymmetricBinding assertions must contain a child protection assertion: ProtectionToken assertion or an EncryptionToken-SignatureToken assertion pair.
entry.suggestion: Add a child protection assertion to the SymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: secpolsymbindtoomanytokens
entry.text: Found SymmetricBinding with too many child protection assertions.
entry.description: A SymmetricBinding assertion has too many child protection assertions. SymmetricBinding assertions must contain a child protection assertion: ProtectionToken assertion or an EncryptionToken-SignatureToken assertion pair. Found a ProtectionToken assertion and an EncryptionToken or SignatureToken assertion.
entry.suggestion: Use a single child protection assertion for the SymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: secpolsymbindnoalgosuite
entry.text: Found SymmetricBinding without a child AlgorithmSuite assertion.
entry.description: A SymmetricBinding assertion did not contain an AlgorithmSuite assertion. SymmetricBinding assertions must contain an AlgorithmSuite assertion.
entry.suggestion: Add a child AlgorithmSuite assertion to the SymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: secpolasymbindnoalgosuite
entry.text: Found AsymmetricBinding without a child AlgorithmSuite assertion.
entry.description: An AsymmetricBinding assertion did not contain an AlgorithmSuite assertion. AsymmetricBinding assertions must contain an AlgorithmSuite assertion.
entry.suggestion: Add a child AlgorithmSuite assertion to the AsymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: secpolenforcenotsign
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Cannot sign a message during enforcement.
entry.description: The DataPower Gateway is not configured to sign messages, so the message must be signed when passing through the DataPower Gateway.
entry.suggestion: To configure the DataPower Gateway to sign a message during enforcement, ensure that you provide all required parameters.

entry.name: secpolenforcenotencrypt
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Cannot encrypt a message during enforcement
entry.description: The DataPower Gateway is not configured to encrypt messages, so the message must be encrypted when passing through the DataPower Gateway.
entry.suggestion: To configure the DataPower Gateway to encrypt a message during enforcement, ensure that you provide all required parameters.

entry.name: secpolunsupportedtoken
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Policy contains unknown token information.
entry.description: See message.
entry.suggestion: Check the policy template to ensure that the token is valid.

entry.name: secpolmisconfiguration
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Misconfiguration.
entry.description: See message.
entry.suggestion: Ensure that the template is properly specified and that you provided all required parameters. For example, if layout assertion requires a timestamp, ensure that the IncludeTimestamp parameter is specified.

entry.name: rmpolwrongsubject
entry.text: WS-Reliable Messaging Policy Mapping: RMAssertion is attached to an improper policy subject
entry.description: An RMAssertion assertion is attached to an improper policy subject. This assertion can be attached to only service and message policy subjects.
entry.suggestion: Associate the RMAssertion to a proper policy subject.

entry.name: secpolenforcetokenmissing
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: During enforcement, cannot generate a token that conforms to the WS-Security Policy.
entry.description: The DataPower Gateway is not configured to generate a token that conforms to the WS-Security Policy, so the message must contain the token when passing through the DataPower Gateway.
entry.suggestion: To configure the DataPower Gateway to generate a token during enforcement, ensure that you provide all required parameters. For example, ensure that you associate an appropriately configured AAA policy.

entry.name: secpolbootstrapnobinding
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Found a BootstrapPolicy assertion without an outer binding.
entry.description: A BootstrapPolicy assertion is an optional child of a SecureConversationToken assertion. The BootstrapPolicy assertion indicates the initial exchange that establishes the relevant security context. This exchange requires a binding assertion to determine the exchange details.
entry.suggestion: Enclose the BootstrapPolicy assertion in a binding, such as a SymmetricBinding or AsymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: secpolbootstrapnochildbinding
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Found a BootstrapPolicy assertion without a child binding assertion.
entry.description: A BootstrapPolicy assertion is an optional child of a SecureConversationToken assertion. The BootstrapPolicy assertion indicates the initial exchange that establishes the relevant security context. The bootstrap assertion requires a child binding assertion to configure this initial exchange.
entry.suggestion: Add a binding as a child of the BootstrapPolicy assertion, such as a SymmetricBinding or AsymmetricBinding assertion.

entry.name: profilecheckerschemaerror
entry.text: Profile Conformance: Schema violation in output from requested checker.
entry.description: A profile conformance request failed because the requested profile checker returned a report that did not conform to the report schema.
entry.suggestion: Verify that the checker xslt delivers a schema-correct report. The schema can be found in store:///schemas/dp-config-conformance-report.xsd

entry.name: wspemptyexactlyone
entry.text: WS-Policy processing discovered an empty assertion.
entry.description: The processing of the WS-Policy discovered an empty assertion. The DataPower Gateway interprets an empty assertion to mean that no input can satisfy policy requirements. Accordingly, the DataPower Gateway generated a policy to reject all input.
entry.suggestion: Verify that your policy does not contain an empty ExactlyOne element.

entry.name: secpolunsupportedtokentype
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: An unknown or unsupported token type is specified in the policy.
entry.description: See message.
entry.suggestion: Verify that the policy uses a supported token type.

entry.name: secpolbootstrapnotfilter
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: A bootstrap policy assertion cannot be processed in filter mode.
entry.description: The effective policy was found to contain a bootstrap policy assertion. This assertion typically generates a RequestSecurityTokenResponse (RSTR) from a RequestSecurityToken (RST) message, which involves altering the message. Altering messages is possible in only enforce mode.
entry.suggestion: Remove the bootstrap policy assertion, or change the policy mode to enforce.

entry.name: secpolsymsignbodyonly
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: WS-SecureConversation digital signatures are over only the SOAP body.
entry.description: According to the WS-SecureConversation specification, support for digital signatures that use derived keys are for signatures over only the SOAP body element.
entry.suggestion: When using WS-SecureConversation derived keys, verify that your policy does not rely on integrity over other message parts.

entry.name: confpolwrongsubject
entry.text: WS-I Conformance Policy Mapping: A conformance requirement is attached to an improper policy subject.
entry.description: A conformance requirement is attached to an improper policy subject. A conformance requirement can be attached to only a service policy subject.
entry.suggestion: Associate the conformance requirement with a service policy subject.

entry.name: confpolunsupportedbinding
entry.text: WS-I Conformance Policy Mapping: Unrecognized binding element.
entry.description: Internal error: Passed an invalid binding element to the mapping stylesheet.
entry.suggestion: Contact IBM Support.

entry.name: secpolnosupporttokenref
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: No support for external references and only partial support for embedded token references.
entry.description: The DataPower Gateway does not support external references (sp:MustSupportRefExternalURI) and only partially supports embedded token references (sp:MustSupportRefEmbeddedToken).
entry.suggestion: Verify that your policy does not contain sp:MustSupportRefExternalURI or sp:MustSuportRefEmbeddedToken.

entry.name: secpolmismatchtokenref
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Mismatch between the X509Token reference and SOAP message security.
entry.description: According to the policy, there is a mismatch between how the token should be referenced in the message versus what the SOAP Message Security option supports.
entry.suggestion: Verify that there is no mismatch between the required X509Token reference and SOAP Message Security Option.

entry.name: secpolembeddedtokenref
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Limited support for embedded token reference.
entry.description: The DataPower Gateway can verify and decrypt a message with an embedded token Reference. However, it does not support signing and encrypting a message with an embedded token reference.
entry.suggestion: Specify a supported token reference in WS-Security Policy.

entry.name: secpolmismatchbindingtoken
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: The asymmetric or symmetric binding does not contain the matched tokens for signing.
entry.description: The binding for signing requires a specific type of tokens, but the security policy does not provide them correctly. The asymmetric binding requires the key-certificate pair, but the binding does not contain the right tokens.
entry.suggestion: Specify the tokens for the binding in the WS-Security Policy.

entry.name: secpolmissingkerberosparam
entry.text: WS-Security Policy Mapping: Required Kerberos parameters not present.
entry.description: A required Kerberos principal or keytab parameter is not configured for this endpoint or operation. For verify operations, the keytab and server principal parameters are required, and the client principal parameter is optional. For sign operations, the keytab, client principal, and server principal parameters are required. If the assertion is attached to a bidirectional WSDL policy subject (service, endpoint, or operation), all three parameters must be provided, as both sign and verify operations will be generated.
entry.suggestion: Specify the required parameters.

entry.name: importfilesystemfull
entry.text: Import: File system full.
entry.description: The import could not complete due to insufficient file system space.
entry.suggestion: Check the content of the file system and remove obsolete and unnecessary files. Files to remove are firmware files in the image: directory or export packages in export: directory.

entry.name: importswitchfailed
entry.text: Import: No domain access.
entry.description: The import could not be completed due to a failure to access a domain. The domain might not exist or was filtered, access to the domain was restricted, or the domain might not be operational.
entry.suggestion: Check that you have valid access to the domain. If you are using a deployment policy, verify that the domain configuration is not being filtered.

entry.name: secpolmissingbootstrap
entry.text: Security Policy: Bootstrap policy is missing.
entry.description: BootstrapPolicy should be attached to operation RequestSecurityToken.
entry.suggestion: Make sure that the correct security policy is attached to the operation, RequestSecurityToken.

entry.description: Nothing is specified in the policy to be signed.

entry.name: policy_bad_source
entry.text: Source type could not be determined automatically.
entry.description: The 'input-map' contains a 'source' attribute value that cannot automatically be identified as JavaScript or XSLT.
entry.suggestion: Verify that the file extension is appropriate for the file type, or use the 'lang' attribute to specify JavaScript or XSLT.

entry.name: policy_bad_lang
entry.text: Invalid 'lang' attribute for 'policy' element.
entry.description: The 'input-map' contains a 'lang' attribute value that is not supported.
entry.suggestion: If the 'lang' attribute is set, it must be one of the following values: 'Default' (automatically determine type), 'JavaScript', or 'XSLT'. Values are case sensitive.

entry.name: policy_bad_state
entry.text: Invalid policy enforcement state.
entry.description: An error occurred while traversing policies in the 'input-map'. The message is rejected.
entry.suggestion: The policy enforcement engine is unable to determine the next policy to enforce. The most frequent cause of this error is that an invalid value was specified for 'next-policy'.

entry.name: policy_bad_uap
entry.text: Unattached policy '%1$s' not found.
entry.description: The 'input-map' contained a policy-name attribute, but the corresponding policy was not found.
entry.suggestion: Submit the policy to the gateway in order for it to be processed correctly. If the policy was submitted, then check to see whether the policy is not yet finished or failed compilation.
